headline: Sentinel Global Announces Close of Inaugural Fund to Back Enterprise Technology Leaders Worldwide
summary: Sentinel Global, a venture capital firm dedicated to connecting visionary founders with real-world adopters, today announced the close of its inaugural fund, Sentinel Fund I, with committed capital totaling $213.5 million. The fund will invest globally in multi-stage enterprise technology companies, with a focus on technologies built for mission-critical performance, regulatory readiness, and scalable deployment across complex systems.
